<dl id="n10138b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10138b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10138b"> 138(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> which? / what are words I first / will hear</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le culte de Mercure <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Il avait aussi un oracle en Acha&iuml;e. Apr&egrave;s beaucoup de c&eacute;r&eacute;monies, on parlait au dieu &agrave; l&apos;oreille, pour lui demander ce qu&apos;on d&eacute;sirait. Ensuite on sortait du temple, les oreilles bouch&eacute;es avec les mains, et <mark>les premi&egrave;res paroles qu&apos;on entendait &eacute;taient la r&eacute;ponse du dieu</mark>. <font color="green">[The cult of Mercury [&hellip;]</font> He also had an oracle in Achaea. After performing many rites one spoke into the god&apos;s ear to request what one desired. Afterwards one went out of the temple, one&apos;s ears stopped with one&apos;s hands, and the first words one heard would be the response of the god.] <small> P. Commelin, <a name="NMGR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#NMGR"><cite title="source">Nouvelle Mythologie</cite></a> (1907) 60</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
